\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces $\lambda $ sweep comparing Ambient GCE and TanGCE at matched $\lambda $ values ($\lambda \in \{0.5, 4.0, 8.0\}$) at layer 8. NL: retrained nonlinear probe accuracy on the target concept (lower = stronger erasure precision). Ambient GCE deteriorates at high $\lambda $, while TanGCE continues improving, supporting the claim that on-manifold updates can safely employ larger erasure strengths.}}{8}{table.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:lambda_sweep}{{3}{8}{$\lambda $ sweep comparing Ambient GCE and TanGCE at matched $\lambda $ values ($\lambda \in \{0.5, 4.0, 8.0\}$) at layer 8. NL: retrained nonlinear probe accuracy on the target concept (lower = stronger erasure precision). Ambient GCE deteriorates at high $\lambda $, while TanGCE continues improving, supporting the claim that on-manifold updates can safely employ larger erasure strengths}{table.3}{}}
