\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces CLIP ViT-B/32 concept erasure on CelebA (validation HPO for $\lambda $). Each method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from the same grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy, ensuring a fair comparison. L/NL Leak: retrained linear / nonlinear probe accuracy on test (lower = better). $\Delta $Ctrl: mean control-task accuracy change across 5 least-correlated attributes (closer to zero = more surgical). Representation: CLIP ViT-B/32 \texttt  {pooler\_output} (768-dim).}}{9}{table.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:celeba_clip_fair}{{4}{9}{CLIP ViT-B/32 concept erasure on CelebA (validation HPO for $\lambda $). Each method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from the same grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy, ensuring a fair comparison. L/NL Leak: retrained linear / nonlinear probe accuracy on test (lower = better). $\Delta $Ctrl: mean control-task accuracy change across 5 least-correlated attributes (closer to zero = more surgical). Representation: CLIP ViT-B/32 \texttt {pooler\_output} (768-dim)}{table.4}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces CelebA all-40-attribute summary (CLIP ViT-B/32, validation HPO for $\lambda $). Each cell averages over all 40 binary CelebA attributes. $\lambda ^*$ is selected per method per concept from the grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation NL probe accuracy. NL Leak: mean nonlinear test accuracy across 40 concepts (lower = better). Mean $\Delta $Ctrl: mean control accuracy change (5 low-correlation controls per concept, averaged over 40 concepts). Worst $\Delta $Ctrl: worst single control drop averaged over 40 concepts.}}{9}{table.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:celeba_clip_all40}{{5}{9}{CelebA all-40-attribute summary (CLIP ViT-B/32, validation HPO for $\lambda $). Each cell averages over all 40 binary CelebA attributes. $\lambda ^*$ is selected per method per concept from the grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation NL probe accuracy. NL Leak: mean nonlinear test accuracy across 40 concepts (lower = better). Mean $\Delta $Ctrl: mean control accuracy change (5 low-correlation controls per concept, averaged over 40 concepts). Worst $\Delta $Ctrl: worst single control drop averaged over 40 concepts}{table.5}{}}
