\newlabel{tab:repo_snapshot_safety}{{8}{12}{Repository snapshot from the iterative safety report at $\lambda =1.0$ after 7 rounds, across layers 8, 16, and 23. Columns T (tangent-constrained) and A (ambient baseline) compare erasure methods. Utility is pairwise helpfulness delta. Leakage and displacement decrease from left to right (lower is better); utility increases from left to right (higher is better). This snapshot table is not a main-text claim anchor and should be read only as evidence of directional consistency with the layer-8 paper-locked row (Table~\ref {tab:full_comparison}). Deeper-layer iterative tangent runs continue to reduce leakage more than ambient baselines across this exploratory sweep}{table.8}{}}
